<div class="container-md px-0">
        <div class="myPollForm rounded px-2 mx-2 my-4" style="margin-bottom: 24px;">
            <form autocomplete="off" id="pollForm" class="py-4 px-1" action="/" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
                <div class="field" id="qField">
                    <label id="qLabel" class="" for="question">Enter poll question</label>
                    <input type="text" class="textInput mb-2" name="question" id="question" required>
                </div>
                <div id="answers" class="hidden">
                    <div class="field ansDiv">
                        <label id="a1Label" class="" for="answer1">Enter first choice</label>
                        <input type="text" class="textInput mb-2" id="answer1" required name="answer1">
                    </div> 
                    <div class="field ansDiv">
                        <label id="a2Label" class="" for="answer2">Enter second choice</label>
                        <input type="text" class="textInput mb-2" id="answer2" required name="answer2">
                    </div>
                    <div id="moreAnswers"></div>
                    
                    <div class="row d-flex justify-content-evenly">
                        <div class="col text-center">
                            <button id="addAnswerBtn" 
                                class="d-inline-block btn-primary rounded mb-sm-4">Add another answer
                            </button>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div id="dupDropdown row mt-4 mb-2"> <!-- A ROW -->
                    </div> <!-- end row dupDropdown -->
                    
                    <div class="container my-5 p-1 border rounded bg-light">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-9 ps-3 pe-0 text-start">
                                <span class="ms-1">
                                    Double-voting protection options
                                </span>
                                <a href="" class="ms-1" id="questMk" data-bs-toggle="modal" 
                                    data-bs-target="#duplicate-check-help" title="More info">
                                    <i class="d-inline-block bi bi-info-circle-fill help-pill" 
                                        style="font-size: 1rem; vertical-align: 5px;">
                                    </i>
                                </a>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-2 align-self-center ms-1 me-2 ps-0 pe-2">
                                <div class="dropdown d-inline-block">
                                    <!-- If you try to add btn class to below, button text overflows -->
                                    <button class="btn-secondary rounded dropdown-toggle d-inline-block" type="button" id="dropdownMenuButton1" data-bs-toggle="dropdown" aria-expanded="false">
                                        <!-- Attempt to prevent users from voting more than once? -->
                                        <span id="dupChoiceSpan">Off</span>
                                    </button>
                                    <ul class="dropdown-menu" aria-labelledby="dropdownMenuButton1">
                                        <li id="dpLi2" class="dpLi"><a class="dropdown-item" href="" id="dpLink2">IP Address-based prevention</a></li>
                                        <li id="dpLi3" class="dpLi" class="dpLi"><a class="dropdown-item" href="" id="dpLink3">Browser cookie-based prevention</a></li>
                                        <li id="dpLi4" class="dpLi"><a class="dropdown-item" href="" id="dpLink4">Use both strategies</a></li>
                                        <li id="dpLi1" class="dpLi"><a class="dropdown-item active" aria-current="true" href="" id="#dpLink1">Off</a></i>
                                    </ul>
                                </div> <!-- end class dropdown -->
                            </div> <!-- end 2nd column -->

                        </div> <!-- end col w-100 -->
                        
                    </div> <!-- end div.container-->
                        
                </div> <!-- end div#answers - the initially hidden bottom part of the form -->
            </form> <!-- end myPollForm -->

            <form method="POST" id="captchaForm" class="">
                <div class="row text-center">
                    <div class="col w-100">
                        <div id="myCaptcha" class="d-inline-block bg-warning bg-light rounded mb-2" style="position: relative">
                            <div class="row m-2"><div class="col">Please solve the captcha & press enter</div></div>
                            <img src='/captcha.jpg' id="captchaImg" class="mx-auto d-block" style="z-index: 1"; /> 
                            <a href="" id="refreshCaptchaLink" data-bs-toggle="tooltip" data-bs-placement="bottom" title="Reload captcha image">
                                <img id="refreshIcon" 
                                    src="/img/misc-icons/noun_Refresh_1247719-100x87.png" 
                                    style="height: 28px; width:26px; position: absolute; bottom: 10px; right: 45px;  z-index: 2"
                                />
                            </a>
                            <div class="col w-100">
                                <input class="d-block mt-2 mb-2 mx-auto ps-3" 
                                minlength="4" 
                                maxlength="4" type="text" name="captcha" id="captcha" 
                                size="4" placeholder="X X X X"
                                style="background-color: lightgray; border: 0" />

                            </div>
                        </div><!-- end #myCaptcha -->
                        
                    </div>
                </div>
            </form>
            <div class="col w-100 text-center">
                            <button id="finishBtn" type="button" class="d-inline-block btn-primary rounded mb-sm-4">Create poll</button>
                        </div>

        </div> <!-- end div.myPollForm -->
    </div> <!-- end container -->

<!-- Modal -->
<div class="modal fade" id="duplicate-check-help" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="dupModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-dialog">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h5 class="modal-title" id="dupModalLabel">Duplicate vote prevention options</h5>
        <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>To discourage users from voting more than once, several strategies can be used. No strategy is foolproof.</p>
        <p><b>Cookie check: </b>A cookie will be set in the visitor's browser when they vote and no further votes will be allowed on this poll once the cookie is set. Note: A determined "cheater" can clear his or her browser cookies or use a different browser to vote more than once to defeat this option.</p>
        <p><b>IP Address check: </b>A visitor's IP address will be recorded and no further votes on this poll will be allowed from that address. Note: Because some environments share a single IP address, e.g. some corporations, schools, & hospitals, this option is not ideal if distributing your survey to multiple recipients in an organization that might be sharing an IP.</p>
        <p><b>Both: </b>Both cookie checks and IP address checks will be performed.</p>
        <p><b>None: </b>No protective measure will be put in place.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>




